		<li class="alt" id="comment-48106">
			<h4 class="comments-author"><a href="http://silentmatt.com/">Matthew Crumley</a> Says:</h4>
			<small class="comments-metadata"><a href="#comment-48106" title="">August 21st, 2010 at 01:01 PM</a></small>
			<p class="comments-entry"><p>I had to do exactly the same thing once when I was in college. I had accidentally deleted a programming project the night before it was due (a disk driver for an operating systems class, ironically). It was fragmented into two parts even, so I had to run grep twice to get the second half of the file.</p>


	<p>It was definitely a good lesson on the value of source control that, unfortunately, I had to learn a few more times before I actually applied it.</p></p>
		</li>
  
